1
00:00:34,801 --> 00:00:37,736
PACU: My name is Pacu.

2
00:00:37,771 --> 00:00:42,265
It's a brand new name,
so I'm not used to it yet,

3
00:00:44,444 --> 00:00:47,208
I'm trying to remember a story,

4
00:00:48,515 --> 00:00:53,214
Sometimes I can,
Sometimes I get mixed up,

5
00:00:53,253 --> 00:00:57,314
Because there's another one
stuck in my head,

6
00:00:58,758 --> 00:01:05,630
It's about me, my brother,
and a shirt in the wind,

7
00:01:16,709 --> 00:01:19,473
The blood is starting
to turn yellow.

8
00:01:19,512 --> 00:01:21,503
[Flapping]

9
00:01:39,332 --> 00:01:40,959
[Wheel creaking]

10
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,490
[Father yelling at oxen]

11
00:01:42,535 --> 00:01:44,935
[Oxen mooing]

12
00:01:44,971 --> 00:01:46,962
[Father yelling]

13
00:01:53,847 --> 00:01:55,678
FATHER: Yah! Yah! Yah!

14
00:02:02,088 --> 00:02:03,817
Yah! Yah! Yah!

15
00:02:03,857 --> 00:02:05,085
[Whips with leaves]

16
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:07,958
Yah! Yah!

17
00:02:07,994 --> 00:02:10,963
PACU: It's Pa who drives
the oxen 'round the mill,

18
00:02:12,332 --> 00:02:15,995
In Grandpa's time,
the slaves did all the work,

19
00:02:16,035 --> 00:02:18,128
[Yelling at oxen]

20
00:02:18,171 --> 00:02:19,866
Now we do it.

21
00:02:19,906 --> 00:02:21,897
[Yelling]

22
00:02:23,209 --> 00:02:25,404
[Liquid dripping]

23
00:02:34,053 --> 00:02:39,719
PACU: Tonio, my brother,
crushes the sugarcane,

24
00:02:39,759 --> 00:02:42,250
Ma gathers the scraps,

25
00:02:42,295 --> 00:02:44,627
[Yelling at oxen]

26
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:46,791
Bring more cane, kid.
Hurry up!

27
00:02:47,934 --> 00:02:49,128
[Flies buzzing]

28
00:02:49,169 --> 00:02:52,229
FATHER: Let's go, Blocky!
Turn, turn!

29
00:02:54,274 --> 00:02:56,071
PACU: Ma says
God never gives us...

30
00:02:56,109 --> 00:02:59,010
heavier burdens
than we can bear,

31
00:02:59,045 --> 00:03:00,842
But God keeps messing up,

32
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:04,839
He sometimes dumps such burdens
on us, we all collapse,

33
00:03:04,884 --> 00:03:08,445
[Yelling at oxen]

34
00:03:10,790 --> 00:03:12,655
We live in Stream-of-Souls,

35
00:03:12,692 --> 00:03:15,183
It's in the middle of nothing,

36
00:03:15,228 --> 00:03:20,222
All we know is it's above
the ground and below the sun,

37
00:03:20,266 --> 00:03:24,430
It's so hot that it
sets our hearts boiling...

38
00:03:24,470 --> 00:03:27,439
like a pot of molasses,

39
00:03:27,473 --> 00:03:29,100
[Flies buzzing]

40
00:03:29,142 --> 00:03:31,110
[Fire crackling]

41
00:03:35,248 --> 00:03:37,239
[Steam hissing]

42
00:03:42,655 --> 00:03:44,623
[Liquid sloshing]

43
00:04:29,068 --> 00:04:30,968
[Bubbling]

44
00:04:38,511 --> 00:04:40,502
[Hissing]

45
00:05:09,876 --> 00:05:12,743
[Raspy breathing]

46
00:05:12,779 --> 00:05:14,770
[Whimpering]

47
00:05:28,227 --> 00:05:30,058
[Gunshot]

48
00:05:40,940 --> 00:05:42,931
[Footsteps]

49
00:05:52,518 --> 00:05:54,349
[Gasps]

50
00:05:55,521 --> 00:05:57,955
[Crickets chirping]

51
00:06:04,897 --> 00:06:09,664
PACU: Tonio, I dreamed
about Incio again,

52
00:06:13,673 --> 00:06:15,766
[Tonio sighs]

53
00:06:18,911 --> 00:06:20,242
Go back to sleep now.

54
00:06:21,414 --> 00:06:22,574
Go on, kid.

55
00:06:24,784 --> 00:06:26,911
[Speaking Portuguese]

56
00:06:26,953 --> 00:06:30,320
[Bed creaking]

57
00:06:38,998 --> 00:06:41,091
TONIO: And now, sleep.

58
00:06:41,134 --> 00:06:42,863
[Flame crackling]

59
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:44,870
[Wind blowing]

60
00:06:44,904 --> 00:06:46,895
[Footsteps]

61
00:06:54,847 --> 00:06:56,838
[Metal squeaking]

62
00:07:27,780 --> 00:07:29,805
[Footsteps]

63
00:07:38,724 --> 00:07:40,715
[Mill grinding]

64
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:44,321
Go on, go on!

65
00:07:44,363 --> 00:07:46,058
[Father yelling at oxen]

66
00:08:04,317 --> 00:08:06,308
[Footsteps]

67
00:08:10,056 --> 00:08:12,047
[Shirt flapping in the wind]

68
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:28,964
[Footsteps]

69
00:08:38,384 --> 00:08:39,908
The blood has turned yellow.

70
00:08:42,655 --> 00:08:46,113
Tonio...

71
00:08:46,158 --> 00:08:48,388
you know what you have to do.

72
00:08:56,769 --> 00:08:59,567
Don't go, Tonio.

73
00:08:59,605 --> 00:09:02,165
Your brother's soul
isn't at rest.

74
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:06,167
He did what he had to do.
It's Tonio's turn now.

75
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:08,540
Don't go.

76
00:09:08,581 --> 00:09:10,048
[Falls to ground]

77
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,757
FATHER: Listen to me, kid,

78
00:09:22,795 --> 00:09:26,424
Your grandfather, your uncles,
your oldest brother...

79
00:09:26,465 --> 00:09:29,798
all died for this land
and for our honor.

80
00:09:31,404 --> 00:09:34,737
One day, it could be you.

81
00:09:34,774 --> 00:09:36,742
You're a Breves,

82
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:41,706
I, too, did my duty.

83
00:09:41,747 --> 00:09:44,773
But it wasn't God's will
that I die.

84
00:09:50,523 --> 00:09:53,959
Tonio, you'll leave
at daybreak,

85
00:09:53,993 --> 00:09:55,187
And remember...

86
00:09:55,227 --> 00:09:58,560
you're only to seek out
your brother's killer.

87
00:09:58,598 --> 00:10:01,465
Man to man, face to face.

88
00:10:06,372 --> 00:10:08,340
[Crickets chirping]

89
00:10:08,374 --> 00:10:10,342
[Footsteps]

90
00:10:10,376 --> 00:10:12,367
[Birds screeching]

91
00:10:29,862 --> 00:10:31,853
[Grass crunching]

92
00:10:40,606 --> 00:10:42,631
[Ropes creaking]

93
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:55,310
[Insects buzzing]

94
00:10:55,354 --> 00:10:57,322
[Birds chirping]

95
00:10:57,356 --> 00:10:59,347
[Grass crunching underfoot]

96
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:11,069
PACU: Tonio will be walking
over land that used to be ours,

97
00:11:11,103 --> 00:11:14,937
The Ferreiras took it from us
and we took it back,

98
00:11:14,974 --> 00:11:17,704
Now it's theirs again,

99
00:11:17,743 --> 00:11:20,109
That's how the feud began,

100
00:11:20,146 --> 00:11:22,910
Pa says it's an eye for an eye,

101
00:11:22,948 --> 00:11:25,678
One of theirs
for one of ours...

102
00:11:25,718 --> 00:11:28,983
and so on, until everyone
ended up blind,

103
00:11:29,021 --> 00:11:30,921
[Bird screeches]

104
00:11:30,956 --> 00:11:33,447
In the land of the blind...

105
00:11:33,492 --> 00:11:36,825
one-eyed people are
said to be mad,

106
00:11:36,862 --> 00:11:38,762
[Crickets chirping]

107
00:11:38,798 --> 00:11:40,789
[Footsteps]

108
00:11:45,004 --> 00:11:46,995
[Cows mooing]

109
00:11:54,980 --> 00:11:56,914
[Insects buzzing]

110
00:11:56,949 --> 00:11:58,940
[Footsteps]

111
00:12:06,659 --> 00:12:09,184
[Woman humming]

112
00:12:24,677 --> 00:12:30,047
MOTHER: May God consent,
may it be God's will,

113
00:12:31,417 --> 00:12:34,181
May the soul of Incio,
my first-born...

114
00:12:34,220 --> 00:12:37,212
find peace alongside his own.

115
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:41,625
May each drop of his blood
cost the enemy two.

116
00:12:41,660 --> 00:12:44,720
May you, my son...

117
00:12:44,764 --> 00:12:47,699
find the peace you never found
among the living.

118
00:12:47,733 --> 00:12:54,730
And watch over your brothers
when their turn comes,

119
00:12:54,774 --> 00:12:58,141
[Humming]

120
00:12:58,177 --> 00:13:00,111
[Cows mooing]

121
00:13:04,049 --> 00:13:06,847
[Rooster crows]

122
00:13:10,222 --> 00:13:12,588
-MAN: We're going for water.
-GU ARD: Yes, sir.

123
00:13:22,935 --> 00:13:24,926
[Cows mooing]

124
00:13:28,207 --> 00:13:29,538
MAN: Everything quiet?

125
00:13:29,575 --> 00:13:31,202
GUARD: Yes, sir,

126
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,627
[Birds chirping]

127
00:13:56,669 --> 00:13:58,660
[Cows mooing]

128
00:14:04,143 --> 00:14:06,668
[Mooing]

129
00:14:06,712 --> 00:14:08,976
[Milk hitting metal bucket]

130
00:14:31,937 --> 00:14:33,404
Like this.

131
00:14:33,439 --> 00:14:35,430
[Milk hitting metal bucket]

132
00:14:37,943 --> 00:14:39,740
[Breathing quickly]

133
00:14:42,948 --> 00:14:44,939
[Tapping]

134
00:14:51,357 --> 00:14:53,621
Go outside, kid.

135
00:15:04,870 --> 00:15:07,065
[Milking continues]

136
00:15:10,075 --> 00:15:12,100
[Milking stops]

137
00:15:12,144 --> 00:15:14,044
[Cow moos]
[Cocks rifle]

138
00:15:14,079 --> 00:15:15,376
For my brother!

139
00:15:19,318 --> 00:15:21,309
[Heavy breathing]

140
00:15:45,678 --> 00:15:47,669
[Men grunting]

141
00:16:01,727 --> 00:16:03,718
[Breathing heavily]

142
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:07,030
[Grunting]

143
00:16:07,066 --> 00:16:09,057
[Breathing heavily]

144
00:16:33,058 --> 00:16:34,355
[Gunshot]

145
00:16:38,130 --> 00:16:39,222
[Thump]

146
00:16:39,264 --> 00:16:41,198
[Panting]

147
00:16:44,336 --> 00:16:46,327
[Gulps]

148
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:10,551
[Man gasping and groaning]

149
00:18:02,514 --> 00:18:04,505
[Gasping]

150
00:18:27,873 --> 00:18:30,000
[Gasping stops]

151
00:18:32,344 --> 00:18:34,335
[Exhales]

152
00:19:09,248 --> 00:19:10,977
[Liquid gurgles]

153
00:19:12,751 --> 00:19:14,742
[Muffled scraping]

154
00:19:20,292 --> 00:19:22,317
[Hoofbeats]

155
00:19:26,565 --> 00:19:29,557
[People singing reverently]

156
00:19:40,312 --> 00:19:42,337
[Sobbing and praying]

157
00:19:46,151 --> 00:19:48,176
[Sobbing]

158
00:19:49,321 --> 00:19:51,380
[Singing]

159
00:19:54,526 --> 00:19:56,551
[Singing]

160
00:20:02,668 --> 00:20:04,693
[Praying]

161
00:20:06,638 --> 00:20:08,663
[Metal jingling]

162
00:20:18,483 --> 00:20:20,246
[Crickets chirping]

163
00:20:24,289 --> 00:20:25,847
[Praying and talking]

164
00:20:25,891 --> 00:20:28,325
[Man praying]

165
00:20:58,090 --> 00:21:01,685
I won't pray for your grandson's
soul, since he killed my son.

166
00:21:01,727 --> 00:21:05,322
But I respect your suffering.
It's the same as mine.

167
00:21:05,364 --> 00:21:07,764
Today, ours is greater.

168
00:21:10,802 --> 00:21:13,600
My son asks permission
to attend the vigil...

169
00:21:13,639 --> 00:21:15,607
to pray for the deceased's soul.

170
00:21:15,641 --> 00:21:19,873
Afterwards, if you accept,
he'd like to talk to you.

171
00:21:25,083 --> 00:21:28,280
-Where is he?
-Outside.

172
00:21:52,844 --> 00:21:55,278
[Talking stops]

173
00:22:03,889 --> 00:22:06,790
[Praying softly]

174
00:22:20,205 --> 00:22:22,537
[Praying and talking resumes]

175
00:23:06,351 --> 00:23:08,410
MR. FERREIRA: Thank you.

176
00:23:09,788 --> 00:23:11,813
MAN: Good-bye, my friend.

177
00:23:11,857 --> 00:23:13,882
[Clock ticking]

178
00:23:23,034 --> 00:23:24,763
I prayed for the deceased.

179
00:23:27,372 --> 00:23:30,205
I came to the wake
and the burial.

180
00:23:33,745 --> 00:23:35,872
Now, I'd like to talk to you.

181
00:23:43,155 --> 00:23:44,918
I request a truce.

182
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:50,951
[Cane tapping]

183
00:23:58,236 --> 00:23:59,260
[Drawer slides]

184
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:04,967
Grandfather,
don't accord a truce.

185
00:24:08,713 --> 00:24:10,704
[Cane tapping]

186
00:24:22,527 --> 00:24:24,222
The truce is granted.

187
00:24:24,262 --> 00:24:26,162
[Tonio exhales]

188
00:24:26,198 --> 00:24:29,656
The same one your father
granted to my grandson.

189
00:24:29,701 --> 00:24:32,829
Until the next moon.

190
00:24:35,707 --> 00:24:40,303
From one death to the next.

191
00:24:41,413 --> 00:24:45,179
This is your guarantee
until the full moon.

192
00:24:45,217 --> 00:24:48,778
After that, when the blood
turns yellow, it will expire.

193
00:25:00,765 --> 00:25:02,756
How old are you?

194
00:25:05,837 --> 00:25:07,464
Twenty.

195
00:25:07,506 --> 00:25:10,532
Your life is now split in two.

196
00:25:11,610 --> 00:25:14,477
The twenty years you've
already lived...

197
00:25:14,513 --> 00:25:17,141
and the short time
you have left.

198
00:25:21,019 --> 00:25:23,180
Have you ever known love?

199
00:25:26,024 --> 00:25:27,821
You never will.

200
00:25:27,859 --> 00:25:30,327
[Clock ticking]

201
00:25:30,362 --> 00:25:33,422
Do you hear that clock?

202
00:25:33,465 --> 00:25:37,629
Each time it ticks--one more,
one more, one more...

203
00:25:39,704 --> 00:25:41,763
it will be telling you...

204
00:25:41,806 --> 00:25:46,971
one less, one less, one less.

205
00:25:47,012 --> 00:25:49,003
[Clock ticking]

206
00:26:00,458 --> 00:26:03,791
[Cows mooing]

207
00:26:29,220 --> 00:26:30,847
[Footsteps]

208
00:26:48,306 --> 00:26:51,537
[Wagon approaches]

209
00:26:56,314 --> 00:26:58,282
Whoa.

210
00:26:58,316 --> 00:26:59,647
Good morning.

211
00:27:00,986 --> 00:27:02,453
Morning.

212
00:27:02,487 --> 00:27:04,512
MAN: Do you know
of a little village...

213
00:27:04,556 --> 00:27:06,717
near here
called Born Sossago?

214
00:27:07,926 --> 00:27:11,123
It's over there.
But it's not little.

215
00:27:11,162 --> 00:27:13,722
MAN: It's not?
What's this place called?

216
00:27:13,765 --> 00:27:15,494
Stream-of-Souls.

217
00:27:17,002 --> 00:27:19,368
So where's the stream?

218
00:27:19,404 --> 00:27:22,703
Dried up.
Only the souls remain.

219
00:27:23,842 --> 00:27:25,332
What is your name?

220
00:27:25,377 --> 00:27:29,108
-Kid.
-WOMAN: What?

221
00:27:29,147 --> 00:27:30,580
I don't have a name.

222
00:27:30,615 --> 00:27:33,379
-What do they call you?
-They just call me kid.

223
00:27:33,418 --> 00:27:36,478
They call the kid "kid."

224
00:27:39,457 --> 00:27:40,754
Kid!

225
00:27:51,469 --> 00:27:54,336
Here, this is for you.

226
00:28:02,047 --> 00:28:04,515
[Harness jingles]

227
00:28:14,526 --> 00:28:15,959
Can you read?

228
00:28:18,396 --> 00:28:20,023
No.

229
00:28:22,867 --> 00:28:25,131
But I can read pictures.

230
00:28:29,274 --> 00:28:31,139
[Wagon leaving]

231
00:28:33,578 --> 00:28:35,170
Hey, kid!

232
00:28:37,348 --> 00:28:39,612
Stay away from those vagrants!

233
00:28:41,886 --> 00:28:43,854
[Hoofbeats]

234
00:28:49,861 --> 00:28:51,761
[Ropes creaking]

235
00:28:51,796 --> 00:28:53,787
[Bird screeching]

236
00:29:56,060 --> 00:29:58,051
[Mother humming]

237
00:30:02,133 --> 00:30:05,330
PACU: Ma thinks the bloodstain
will come out,

238
00:30:06,938 --> 00:30:09,304
[Humming]

239
00:30:09,340 --> 00:30:11,774
But it won't come out,

240
00:30:13,311 --> 00:30:14,778
[Water swishing]

241
00:30:14,813 --> 00:30:17,509
[Humming]

242
00:30:22,487 --> 00:30:24,614
FATHER: You did your duty,
my son,

243
00:30:24,656 --> 00:30:28,456
Now you have much to do
before the next moon.

244
00:30:28,493 --> 00:30:30,427
Crush the sugarcane
and fix the roof...

245
00:30:30,461 --> 00:30:32,793
in case it rains this year.

246
00:30:32,831 --> 00:30:33,991
It never rains.

247
00:30:35,667 --> 00:30:39,603
Then the raw sugar
has to be sold in the village.

248
00:30:39,637 --> 00:30:41,605
[Heavy breathing,
leaves rustling]

249
00:30:46,644 --> 00:30:49,875
[Groaning softly]

250
00:30:49,914 --> 00:30:51,905
[Inhales sharply]

251
00:30:54,953 --> 00:30:58,753
[Sighs]

252
00:30:58,790 --> 00:31:00,849
PACU: That sounded like
a bad dream, Tonio,

253
00:31:00,892 --> 00:31:04,623
I tried to wake you up,
but you didn't want to,

254
00:31:06,531 --> 00:31:08,795
What are you doing up, kid?

255
00:31:08,833 --> 00:31:10,664
Reading.

256
00:31:12,470 --> 00:31:14,495
Where'd you get that?

257
00:31:14,539 --> 00:31:15,801
A present.

258
00:31:17,141 --> 00:31:18,403
From who?

259
00:31:18,443 --> 00:31:21,173
The girl gave it to me.

260
00:31:21,212 --> 00:31:22,577
What girl?

261
00:31:22,614 --> 00:31:25,276
My friend, of course.

262
00:31:25,316 --> 00:31:29,082
-You went into town alone?
-PACU: No.

263
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:30,781
They were lost.

264
00:31:30,822 --> 00:31:33,848
But not anymore.
I showed them the way.

265
00:31:33,892 --> 00:31:34,950
Hmm.

266
00:31:38,229 --> 00:31:41,687
So what's that book about?

267
00:31:41,733 --> 00:31:44,031
It's about everything.

268
00:31:52,543 --> 00:31:54,534
[Tonio chuckles]

269
00:31:57,849 --> 00:31:59,976
Something's wrong, kid.

270
00:32:00,018 --> 00:32:02,612
-What's wrong?
-It's upside down.

271
00:32:03,955 --> 00:32:06,947
No, it's not.
Want to bet?

272
00:32:17,635 --> 00:32:19,967
It's the same this way...

273
00:32:20,004 --> 00:32:21,972
or that way.

274
00:32:22,006 --> 00:32:23,701
No difference, see?

275
00:32:25,209 --> 00:32:28,406
You don't know a thing
about books. Give it to me.

276
00:32:35,386 --> 00:32:37,650
-PACU: It's her!
-TONIO: Her? Who?

277
00:32:37,689 --> 00:32:39,486
The girl who gave me the book.

278
00:32:41,492 --> 00:32:46,953
She lives in the sea with the
fish, the crabs, and the boats.

279
00:32:46,998 --> 00:32:49,728
She'll take me with her.

280
00:32:49,767 --> 00:32:52,861
She'll teach me
the alphabet and all.

281
00:32:52,904 --> 00:32:54,132
You don't believe me?

282
00:32:55,506 --> 00:32:58,202
When I grow up,
we'll get married.

283
00:32:58,242 --> 00:33:00,904
-Has she been informed?
-No.

284
00:33:00,945 --> 00:33:02,845
It's still a secret.

285
00:33:14,125 --> 00:33:16,787
[Father speaking to oxen]

286
00:33:16,828 --> 00:33:18,819
[Wheels clattering]

287
00:33:38,416 --> 00:33:40,316
[Wheels squeaking]

288
00:33:55,933 --> 00:33:57,901
PACU: One day...

289
00:33:57,935 --> 00:34:01,837
the mermaid comes up
to the surface.

290
00:34:05,043 --> 00:34:14,111
And she saw the tree, the cows,
the mountains, and grass.

291
00:34:14,152 --> 00:34:17,280
When she looked at the top of
the raw-sugar house...

292
00:34:17,321 --> 00:34:20,552
she saw the rooster with the
mangy neck crowing for her.

293
00:34:20,591 --> 00:34:22,718
[Crows like a rooster]

294
00:34:22,760 --> 00:34:23,784
Ahh.

295
00:34:23,828 --> 00:34:25,193
Wow, she really liked that!

296
00:34:25,229 --> 00:34:33,193
And she also saw
the sugarcane, the mill...

297
00:34:33,237 --> 00:34:34,636
everything delighted her!

298
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:40,277
But the best part of all
was when she saw the kid.

299
00:34:40,311 --> 00:34:42,939
Are you still reading that book?

300
00:34:42,980 --> 00:34:45,175
Can't you see it will
hurt your eyes?

301
00:34:45,216 --> 00:34:47,878
I'm trying to remember
the story.

302
00:34:47,919 --> 00:34:50,717
Sometimes I can,
sometimes I forget.

303
00:34:50,755 --> 00:34:52,245
Then just forget.

304
00:34:57,829 --> 00:35:00,798
[Cows mooing]

305
00:35:00,832 --> 00:35:02,629
MR. FERREIRA: Well?

306
00:35:04,368 --> 00:35:06,495
It is beginning to change color.

307
00:35:08,039 --> 00:35:10,439
It won't take long now.

308
00:35:10,475 --> 00:35:11,635
No, it won't.

309
00:35:20,251 --> 00:35:22,185
[Mr. Lourenco sighs]

310
00:35:25,790 --> 00:35:28,156
[Rummaging in drawer]

311
00:35:32,663 --> 00:35:33,960
[Clink]

312
00:35:50,081 --> 00:35:52,709
You're the most important
merchant in town...

313
00:35:52,750 --> 00:35:58,518
but with all due respect,
this isn't the right amount.

314
00:35:58,556 --> 00:36:01,616
MR LOURENCO: No,
It is the right amount,

315
00:36:01,659 --> 00:36:04,423
But I gave you
the usual quantity.

316
00:36:04,462 --> 00:36:09,764
Steam power is bringing
the price down. It's progress.

317
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:14,464
I think you should follow
the example, Mr. Breves.

318
00:36:14,505 --> 00:36:17,167
But Mr. Lourenco,
we had an agreement.

319
00:36:17,208 --> 00:36:19,676
There is no shortage
of raw sugar!

320
00:36:20,778 --> 00:36:24,236
[Singing and drumming]

321
00:36:24,282 --> 00:36:26,273
[Children yelling]

322
00:36:32,490 --> 00:36:37,518
[Man singing]

323
00:36:46,337 --> 00:36:48,430
[Singing and drumming continue]

324
00:36:51,042 --> 00:36:53,670
MAN: Come on up!

325
00:36:53,711 --> 00:36:56,805
Come one, come all,
if you want to watch...

326
00:36:56,847 --> 00:36:58,337
the snake and the toad dance!

327
00:36:58,382 --> 00:37:01,408
[Children cheering]

328
00:37:01,452 --> 00:37:06,515
Everyone will come.
Together we will go.

329
00:37:06,557 --> 00:37:08,752
[Cheering]

330
00:37:08,793 --> 00:37:11,728
Tomorrow night,
no one will sleep.

331
00:37:11,762 --> 00:37:13,662
No man, no woman, no child.

332
00:37:13,698 --> 00:37:15,757
[Children cheering]

333
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:17,597
Come one, come all!

334
00:37:17,635 --> 00:37:19,500
CHILDREN: To the circus!

335
00:37:19,537 --> 00:37:21,505
[Drumming continues]

336
00:37:21,539 --> 00:37:23,564
[Wheels rumbling]

337
00:37:35,620 --> 00:37:38,817
Mr. Lourenco wants to decide
other people's suffering.

338
00:37:44,729 --> 00:37:46,060
[Leaves tearing]

339
00:37:46,097 --> 00:37:47,758
[Chopping]

340
00:38:05,182 --> 00:38:06,581
I saw her.

341
00:38:06,617 --> 00:38:09,484
Who?

342
00:38:09,520 --> 00:38:12,182
The mermaid.

343
00:38:12,223 --> 00:38:14,088
Up on stilts.

344
00:38:15,092 --> 00:38:17,219
On what?

345
00:38:17,261 --> 00:38:19,058
She's in the circus.

346
00:38:19,096 --> 00:38:21,064
Yeah?

347
00:38:21,098 --> 00:38:23,658
They're bringing
the circus to town...

348
00:38:23,701 --> 00:38:26,864
with a fire-eater, a clown...

349
00:38:26,904 --> 00:38:28,531
and a snake that dances
with a toad.

350
00:38:28,572 --> 00:38:31,837
-A snake with a what?
-A toad.

351
00:38:31,876 --> 00:38:34,606
Yeah?

352
00:38:38,649 --> 00:38:40,514
[Mill grinding]

353
00:38:40,551 --> 00:38:43,042
[Speaking to oxen]

354
00:38:51,228 --> 00:38:54,288
Hey, are you daydreaming, kid?
More cane!

355
00:38:54,332 --> 00:38:57,495
Keep turning!

356
00:39:00,404 --> 00:39:02,463
FATHER: Hurry up
with that cane!

357
00:39:03,841 --> 00:39:05,741
[Yelling]
[Whip snaps]

358
00:39:18,522 --> 00:39:21,650
[Ox eating]

359
00:39:21,692 --> 00:39:23,091
Tonio.

360
00:39:24,362 --> 00:39:26,887
I want to go to the circus
real bad.

361
00:39:29,166 --> 00:39:30,599
You think Pa will let you?

362
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:34,395
We're like oxen here.

363
00:39:34,438 --> 00:39:36,372
We go 'round and 'round
and never go anywhere.

364
00:39:41,112 --> 00:39:43,012
[Door creaks]

365
00:40:02,199 --> 00:40:04,633
[Sighs]

366
00:40:18,249 --> 00:40:19,944
Let's go, kid.

367
00:40:26,590 --> 00:40:28,649
You want to see the circus?

368
00:40:28,692 --> 00:40:30,091
Hmm?

369
00:40:31,228 --> 00:40:32,855
Then let's go.

370
00:40:41,238 --> 00:40:42,535
[Fire roaring]

371
00:40:42,573 --> 00:40:44,905
[Crowd cheering and clapping]

372
00:40:44,942 --> 00:40:46,239
[Roar]

373
00:40:46,277 --> 00:40:48,541
[Cheering]

374
00:40:48,579 --> 00:40:50,103
[Roar]

375
00:40:50,147 --> 00:40:52,945
[Roar]

376
00:40:52,983 --> 00:40:54,177
[Roar]

377
00:40:55,619 --> 00:40:59,111
See? I told you,
she's hot stuff.

378
00:40:59,156 --> 00:41:00,316
[Laughs]

379
00:41:00,357 --> 00:41:01,619
[Fire roars]

380
00:41:03,427 --> 00:41:05,258
[R oars]

381
00:41:05,296 --> 00:41:07,196
[R oars]

382
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:11,825
[Fire roars]

383
00:41:12,937 --> 00:41:14,529
[Roars]

384
00:41:16,907 --> 00:41:18,204
[Roars]

385
00:41:18,242 --> 00:41:19,402
[Roars]

386
00:41:33,924 --> 00:41:35,755
[Cheering]

387
00:41:48,439 --> 00:41:50,373
[Crowd cheers]

388
00:42:00,985 --> 00:42:03,419
[Crowd cheers louder]

389
00:42:03,454 --> 00:42:05,217
[Shouting and cheering]

390
00:42:09,727 --> 00:42:12,719
CROWD: Fire! Fire!

391
00:42:12,763 --> 00:42:14,390
[Crowd yelling]

392
00:42:28,546 --> 00:42:30,537
[Crowd laughing]

393
00:42:32,149 --> 00:42:33,946
[Chuckles]

394
00:42:33,984 --> 00:42:36,851
I'll be damned!
I'm toasted!

395
00:42:36,887 --> 00:42:38,718
[Laughing]

396
00:42:39,823 --> 00:42:41,723
[Crates thumping]

397
00:42:53,504 --> 00:42:56,439
Salustiana, look who's here.

398
00:42:58,342 --> 00:43:01,436
Hey! It's the kid
without a name.

399
00:43:03,447 --> 00:43:06,348
Anything's better
than Salustiana.

400
00:43:08,419 --> 00:43:10,944
[Equipment rattles]

401
00:43:17,194 --> 00:43:19,685
My name's Clara.

402
00:43:19,730 --> 00:43:20,697
What's yours?

403
00:43:20,731 --> 00:43:23,029
That's Tonio, my brother.

404
00:43:24,535 --> 00:43:26,002
Good evening.

405
00:43:27,705 --> 00:43:29,172
Did you like the show?

406
00:43:29,206 --> 00:43:33,302
I liked the fire best.
You're really hot!

407
00:43:52,896 --> 00:43:54,363
Holy shit!

408
00:44:00,371 --> 00:44:03,431
I brought the book so you can
remind me of the story.

409
00:44:03,474 --> 00:44:05,169
It's late now.

410
00:44:14,385 --> 00:44:16,717
SALUSTIANA: Hey, kid...

411
00:44:16,754 --> 00:44:20,884
I'm going to give you a name.
A name all your own.

412
00:44:20,924 --> 00:44:23,085
What's your favorite animal?

413
00:44:24,461 --> 00:44:26,224
Do you like birds?

414
00:44:27,431 --> 00:44:29,296
He only likes sea creatures.

415
00:44:29,333 --> 00:44:32,268
Oh, yeah? Then I'll
name you Sardine!

416
00:44:32,302 --> 00:44:33,269
Ha ha!

417
00:44:33,303 --> 00:44:35,703
You bullshitting me?

418
00:44:35,739 --> 00:44:37,366
We'll choose another name.

419
00:44:40,177 --> 00:44:41,303
Pacu.

420
00:44:41,345 --> 00:44:43,609
Pacu!

421
00:44:43,647 --> 00:44:46,445
I've christened you,

422
00:44:46,483 --> 00:44:48,974
You have a name now.

423
00:44:51,355 --> 00:44:53,619
And I'm your godfather,

424
00:44:53,657 --> 00:44:54,749
Hmm!

425
00:44:54,792 --> 00:44:56,885
To celebrate your christening!

426
00:44:58,162 --> 00:45:00,062
[Salustiana laughs]

427
00:45:07,137 --> 00:45:09,765
[Crickets chirping]
[Hoofbeats]

428
00:45:09,807 --> 00:45:12,605
-PACU: I don't like it,
-TONIO: What?

429
00:45:12,643 --> 00:45:14,235
The name.

430
00:45:14,278 --> 00:45:15,643
Pacu.

431
00:45:17,047 --> 00:45:20,915
He's pulling my leg.
Pacu is a kind of river fish.

432
00:45:24,655 --> 00:45:25,713
Tonio.

433
00:45:27,257 --> 00:45:29,589
Do you think
they sleep together?

434
00:45:32,463 --> 00:45:33,691
I don't know.

435
00:45:36,500 --> 00:45:39,560
All I know is,
he's your godfather now.

436
00:45:39,603 --> 00:45:41,002
Pacu.

437
00:45:42,673 --> 00:45:44,163
Pacu!

438
00:45:44,208 --> 00:45:45,971
TONIO: Pacu!

439
00:45:46,009 --> 00:45:47,203
[Tonio laughs]

440
00:45:47,244 --> 00:45:50,771
TONIO: Pacu! Ha ha!

441
00:45:50,814 --> 00:45:52,645
Cut it out, will you?

442
00:45:52,683 --> 00:45:54,674
[Crickets chirping]

443
00:46:05,963 --> 00:46:07,453
Where'd you take the kid?

444
00:46:09,399 --> 00:46:11,094
Where?

445
00:46:12,102 --> 00:46:14,332
To the circus.

446
00:46:14,371 --> 00:46:15,463
Where?

447
00:46:17,374 --> 00:46:19,342
The circus.

448
00:46:19,376 --> 00:46:20,502
Go to your room, kid.

449
00:46:21,545 --> 00:46:22,569
Right now!

450
00:46:24,882 --> 00:46:27,578
[Sighs]

451
00:46:29,186 --> 00:46:32,155
FATHER: Having fun
at a time like this?

452
00:46:32,189 --> 00:46:35,488
Have you no respect
for our dead?

453
00:46:37,327 --> 00:46:40,353
You should follow
your older brother's example.

454
00:46:40,397 --> 00:46:41,659
Don't worry.

455
00:46:44,768 --> 00:46:47,168
I'll soon be like him.

456
00:46:47,204 --> 00:46:49,866
Shut up.

457
00:46:49,907 --> 00:46:52,171
Sorry, but I won't shut up.

458
00:46:52,209 --> 00:46:54,507
[Breathes heavily]

459
00:46:57,815 --> 00:47:00,409
-Shut your mouth.
-No!

460
00:47:00,450 --> 00:47:03,112
-Shut up!
-No!

461
00:47:03,153 --> 00:47:04,518
[Swings whip]
[Father grunts]

462
00:47:04,555 --> 00:47:06,216
-FATHER: Shut up!
-TONIO: No!

463
00:47:06,256 --> 00:47:09,020
[Swings whip]

464
00:47:09,059 --> 00:47:10,549
-I won't!
-Shut up!

465
00:47:10,594 --> 00:47:13,290
[Flame roars, then sputters]

466
00:47:14,598 --> 00:47:16,395
[Breathing heavily]

467
00:47:18,468 --> 00:47:19,992
[Crickets chirping]

468
00:47:27,277 --> 00:47:28,869
PACU: Tonio,

469
00:47:31,348 --> 00:47:33,748
You have to go away.

470
00:47:41,525 --> 00:47:43,550
[Crickets chirping]

471
00:47:49,166 --> 00:47:50,895
Did you see his black armband?

472
00:47:55,172 --> 00:47:56,799
Yes.

473
00:47:56,840 --> 00:47:59,331
He won't be around much longer.

474
00:47:59,376 --> 00:48:02,709
-What are you talking about?
-It's true.

475
00:48:02,746 --> 00:48:04,270
It's a family feud.

476
00:48:04,314 --> 00:48:07,772
One side kills, then the other.

477
00:48:07,818 --> 00:48:11,948
-How do you know?
-It goes way back.

478
00:48:11,989 --> 00:48:14,981
They're fighting for the land.

479
00:48:15,025 --> 00:48:18,358
They'd rather kill
than solve their problems.

480
00:48:18,395 --> 00:48:20,920
Real fanatics.

481
00:48:20,964 --> 00:48:23,660
It's like the two snakes
I saw fighting.

482
00:48:23,700 --> 00:48:27,261
Each was biting the tail
of the other.

483
00:48:27,304 --> 00:48:31,707
They ate each other up
until nothing was left.

484
00:48:31,742 --> 00:48:35,178
Nothing but a pool of blood
on the ground.

485
00:48:35,212 --> 00:48:37,339
They'll all be killed off.

486
00:48:37,381 --> 00:48:39,076
Hmm.

487
00:48:39,116 --> 00:48:42,847
I feel sorry for them.
I really do.

488
00:48:44,655 --> 00:48:46,179
Yah!

489
00:48:46,223 --> 00:48:49,454
Stay in line!
Keep it going, Slowpoke!

490
00:48:49,493 --> 00:48:52,257
[Mill creaking]

491
00:48:56,166 --> 00:48:58,691
FATHER: You're lagging!

492
00:48:58,735 --> 00:49:02,068
Keep turning!
Come on, Blocky!

493
00:49:02,105 --> 00:49:04,164
Keep it going!

494
00:49:04,207 --> 00:49:06,368
Come on, Slowpoke!

495
00:49:06,410 --> 00:49:08,139
[Yelling]

496
00:49:08,178 --> 00:49:09,167
[Snorts]

497
00:49:10,447 --> 00:49:11,880
[Yells]

498
00:49:11,915 --> 00:49:13,849
[Yells and whips oxen
with leaves]

499
00:49:13,884 --> 00:49:15,784
[Father yelling]

500
00:49:15,819 --> 00:49:18,049
[Oxen snorting]

501
00:49:18,088 --> 00:49:20,852
[Cogs creaking]

502
00:49:20,891 --> 00:49:22,791
[Liquid dripping]

503
00:49:25,495 --> 00:49:27,190
[Dripping slows, then stops]

504
00:49:27,230 --> 00:49:29,755
[Oxen breathing heavily]

505
00:49:38,275 --> 00:49:41,108
[Ox moos]

506
00:49:51,888 --> 00:49:53,788
[Men grunting]

507
00:49:55,492 --> 00:49:58,620
FATHER: Get up, Slowpoke!

508
00:49:58,662 --> 00:50:00,960
[Ox moos loudly]

509
00:50:00,998 --> 00:50:03,330
That's good, my ox.

510
00:50:09,940 --> 00:50:11,237
[Hoofbeats]

511
00:50:11,274 --> 00:50:12,434
Tonio!

512
00:50:14,945 --> 00:50:17,573
The oxen are going 'round
on their own!

513
00:50:28,992 --> 00:50:30,323
[Yoke clatters]

514
00:50:38,869 --> 00:50:40,860
[Birds chirping]

515
00:51:04,661 --> 00:51:08,062
[Liquid pouring]

516
00:51:08,098 --> 00:51:10,157
[Dishes rattling]

517
00:51:17,941 --> 00:51:19,909
[People chattering]

518
00:51:19,943 --> 00:51:21,934
[Dog barking]

519
00:51:26,450 --> 00:51:27,747
Need some help?

520
00:51:28,752 --> 00:51:31,186
I can always use help.

521
00:51:32,823 --> 00:51:34,415
Especially if it's free.

522
00:51:54,211 --> 00:51:55,803
[Thump]

523
00:51:57,247 --> 00:51:59,647
Where's my godson?

524
00:51:59,683 --> 00:52:01,310
At home.

525
00:52:01,351 --> 00:52:03,751
Come for the circus?

526
00:52:03,787 --> 00:52:04,947
Heh!

527
00:52:04,988 --> 00:52:07,718
You'll have to wait
till next year.

528
00:52:07,757 --> 00:52:10,521
We're off to Ventura
for the festival.

529
00:52:16,666 --> 00:52:18,531
Ever been to Ventura?

530
00:52:18,568 --> 00:52:22,527
No. I haven't been anywhere.

531
00:52:26,576 --> 00:52:29,704
[Hoofbeats]

532
00:52:29,746 --> 00:52:31,941
[Whip cracks]

533
00:52:36,319 --> 00:52:38,310
[Wheels rumbling]

534
00:52:52,602 --> 00:52:54,627
SALUSTIANA: Were you born
dead or alive?

535
00:52:54,671 --> 00:52:56,696
TONIO: What?

536
00:52:56,740 --> 00:52:58,640
SALUSTIANA: Were you born
dead or alive?

537
00:53:00,644 --> 00:53:01,611
TONIO: Alive.

538
00:53:01,645 --> 00:53:05,581
Well, I was born dead.
True or false?

539
00:53:05,615 --> 00:53:07,173
True, I'm afraid.

540
00:53:07,217 --> 00:53:08,184
Ha ha!

541
00:53:08,218 --> 00:53:09,947
Let me explain.

542
00:53:09,986 --> 00:53:12,819
My mother almost died
giving birth.

543
00:53:12,856 --> 00:53:16,189
I was born purple--so purple
they thought I was dead.

544
00:53:16,226 --> 00:53:17,591
True or false?

545
00:53:17,627 --> 00:53:22,530
They ignored me for two hours
while trying to save my mother.

546
00:53:22,566 --> 00:53:27,629
Then they decided to wash me so
I'd look decent for the funeral.

547
00:53:27,671 --> 00:53:31,368
As soon as I felt the cold
water, I started howling.

548
00:53:31,408 --> 00:53:35,105
As a result, that was
my first and last bath.

549
00:53:35,145 --> 00:53:36,772
No more baths!

550
00:53:36,813 --> 00:53:39,611
And the second result:
Nothing bothers me.

551
00:53:39,649 --> 00:53:42,880
Anyone born dead has
been through the worst.

552
00:53:42,919 --> 00:53:46,548
After that, life's a breeze.
No kidding!

553
00:53:50,093 --> 00:53:51,958
So when it comes to water...

554
00:53:51,995 --> 00:53:54,896
I don't even use it
for drinking!

555
00:53:54,931 --> 00:53:55,989
Ha ha ha!

556
00:53:56,032 --> 00:53:58,933
Yuck! Let's go, Bootleg!

557
00:54:22,592 --> 00:54:23,752
[Snaps reins]

558
00:54:23,793 --> 00:54:25,761
[Harness jangles]

559
00:54:30,934 --> 00:54:32,902
[Fire crackling]

560
00:54:39,476 --> 00:54:40,943
[Bottle clanks]

561
00:54:45,515 --> 00:54:47,676
[Fabric rustles]

562
00:54:53,156 --> 00:54:55,647
[Salustiana sighs]

563
00:55:36,833 --> 00:55:38,300
How long do you have?

564
00:55:39,536 --> 00:55:41,663
Not long.

565
00:55:41,705 --> 00:55:47,166
I'll go as far as Ventura,
then I have to go back,

566
00:55:52,182 --> 00:55:54,412
SALUSTIANA: Clara...

567
00:55:54,451 --> 00:55:56,078
where are you?

568
00:56:20,910 --> 00:56:22,878
[Footsteps]

569
00:56:24,314 --> 00:56:26,578
[Wind blowing, leaves rustling]

570
00:56:50,173 --> 00:56:52,232
[Door creaks]

571
00:57:08,291 --> 00:57:11,590
In this house, the dead
command the living.

572
00:57:22,572 --> 00:57:26,133
MOTHER: Sometimes I wish Tonio
wouldn't come back.

573
00:57:30,447 --> 00:57:32,540
FATHER:
Don't say that, woman.

574
00:57:35,852 --> 00:57:38,320
MOTHER: Even the worst life
is better...

575
00:57:38,354 --> 00:57:40,584
than being slaughtered
like an animal.

576
00:57:50,467 --> 00:57:52,492
Look around you, woman.

577
00:57:53,970 --> 00:57:55,631
What do we have left?

578
00:58:06,349 --> 00:58:08,044
Nothing.

579
00:58:11,354 --> 00:58:16,223
You see, we've already
lost everything.

580
00:58:18,528 --> 00:58:22,897
And if Tonio doesn't come back,
we'll have lost our honor, too.

581
00:58:25,802 --> 00:58:27,770
[Wheels rumbling]

582
00:58:27,804 --> 00:58:30,102
SALUSTIANA:
Let's go, Bootleg!

583
00:58:32,008 --> 00:58:33,737
Come on, Bootleg!

584
00:58:35,078 --> 00:58:37,876
Sleep well, young man?

585
00:58:40,216 --> 00:58:42,878
PACU: The mermaid
couldn't live on land...

586
00:58:42,919 --> 00:58:45,547
because she had
a fish-tail...

587
00:58:45,588 --> 00:58:47,988
where her legs should be.

588
00:58:48,024 --> 00:58:51,482
The poor thing couldn't walk.

589
00:58:51,528 --> 00:58:53,519
[Chopping]

590
00:58:53,563 --> 00:58:57,499
Even so, one day she got furious
and jumped out of the sea!

591
00:58:57,534 --> 00:59:01,732
She started fighting
with snakes and toads.

592
00:59:03,072 --> 00:59:08,009
Then, because she missed
the kid so much...

593
00:59:09,345 --> 00:59:12,371
she started puffing out
fire and smoke.

594
00:59:12,415 --> 00:59:13,541
[Chopping]

595
00:59:13,583 --> 00:59:17,019
So the kid got
on a tired old ox...

596
00:59:17,053 --> 00:59:20,147
and galloped after the mermaid,

597
00:59:20,189 --> 00:59:23,056
Do-dum, do-dum,
looking for the mermaid.

598
00:59:23,092 --> 00:59:25,959
He went through the woods,
the cane fields...

599
00:59:25,995 --> 00:59:29,055
and when he parted
the last row of sugarcane...

600
00:59:31,834 --> 00:59:33,358
he came upon the sea.

601
00:59:36,172 --> 00:59:38,697
[Rapid footsteps]

602
00:59:38,741 --> 00:59:41,209
And he found the mermaid.

603
00:59:45,415 --> 00:59:47,542
Following
in your brother's footsteps?

604
00:59:47,584 --> 00:59:50,018
Think you can just
take it easy around here?

605
00:59:50,053 --> 00:59:51,987
PACU: Give me my book!

606
00:59:52,021 --> 00:59:54,489
Give it to me!

607
00:59:57,694 --> 00:59:59,286
Give me my book!

608
00:59:59,329 --> 01:00:01,194
Give it to me!

609
01:00:01,230 --> 01:00:03,130
GROUP: Die, you rabid dog!

610
01:00:03,166 --> 01:00:05,031
Take that!
To hell with the traitor!

611
01:00:08,738 --> 01:00:10,933
Hah!

612
01:00:10,974 --> 01:00:13,568
[Children shouting]

613
01:00:18,681 --> 01:00:22,048
MAN: Don't tell me this
shitty circus is still around,

614
01:00:22,085 --> 01:00:24,553
What did you say?

615
01:00:24,587 --> 01:00:26,612
MAN: You heard me,

616
01:00:26,656 --> 01:00:28,715
-Shit what?
-MAN: Circus!

617
01:00:32,595 --> 01:00:35,496
-SALUSTIANA: Get out of here!
-MAN: You lousy bum!

618
01:00:35,531 --> 01:00:36,862
Ha ha ha!

619
01:00:36,899 --> 01:00:40,562
Reginaldo. Come here!

620
01:00:40,603 --> 01:00:43,299
Shitty things are impossible
to get rid of. Like you.

621
01:00:43,339 --> 01:00:45,432
You mean like you.

622
01:00:45,475 --> 01:00:48,103
[Men laughing]

623
01:00:48,144 --> 01:00:50,305
REGINALDO: Is that Clara?

624
01:00:50,346 --> 01:00:51,711
Your stepdaughter?

625
01:00:51,748 --> 01:00:53,409
Spitting image of her mother.

626
01:00:53,449 --> 01:00:55,440
REGINALDO: How she's grown!

627
01:00:56,953 --> 01:00:58,944
[Liquid burbling]

628
01:01:01,991 --> 01:01:05,051
Do it right, kid.
You're big enough now.

629
01:01:12,135 --> 01:01:14,399
[People talking and clapping]

630
01:01:16,172 --> 01:01:18,163
[Drum playing]

631
01:01:23,680 --> 01:01:25,671
[Cheering and clapping]

632
01:01:38,194 --> 01:01:39,752
Come, Tonio.

633
01:01:46,335 --> 01:01:48,030
I'm going to show you
something, Tonio.

634
01:01:50,039 --> 01:01:54,408
Help me. Pull on the rope.

635
01:02:09,525 --> 01:02:12,722
CLARA: Start turning,

636
01:02:13,830 --> 01:02:15,730
Turn it faster, Tonio.

637
01:02:15,765 --> 01:02:17,756
[Breathing rapidly]

638
01:02:20,169 --> 01:02:21,363
Faster!

639
01:02:28,811 --> 01:02:29,971
Faster!

640
01:02:34,617 --> 01:02:36,107
Even more!

641
01:02:53,436 --> 01:02:55,427
[Clara yelling
in Portuguese]

642
01:03:06,249 --> 01:03:08,877
[Clara laughing]

643
01:03:23,833 --> 01:03:26,097
[Clara laughing continues]

644
01:03:38,981 --> 01:03:40,505
[Drums beating]

645
01:03:40,550 --> 01:03:42,541
[People talking]

646
01:03:46,422 --> 01:03:48,913
[Both breathing heavily]

647
01:04:09,879 --> 01:04:12,677
TONIO: I'll never forget this...

648
01:04:12,715 --> 01:04:14,307
or you.

649
01:04:14,350 --> 01:04:16,147
CLARA: Neither will I, Tonio.

650
01:04:19,455 --> 01:04:20,854
SALUSTIANA: Clara!

651
01:04:31,667 --> 01:04:33,601
[Crowd chanting and clapping]

652
01:04:41,377 --> 01:04:42,935
[Crickets chirping]

653
01:04:46,315 --> 01:04:48,283
[Mill grinding]

654
01:04:53,122 --> 01:04:54,851
[Father yelling at oxen,
whips with leaves]

655
01:04:59,061 --> 01:05:01,552
FATHER: Yah! Yah!
Yah! Yah! Yah!

656
01:05:10,606 --> 01:05:12,073
Whoa.

657
01:05:12,108 --> 01:05:14,235
[Mill stops grinding]

658
01:05:43,239 --> 01:05:44,206
Yah!
[Whips]

659
01:05:44,240 --> 01:05:46,572
[Mill grinding]

660
01:05:46,609 --> 01:05:48,600
[Father yelling at oxen]

661
01:06:05,995 --> 01:06:09,692
The shirt is almost yellow now.

662
01:06:09,732 --> 01:06:14,226
It always turns yellow.

663
01:06:14,270 --> 01:06:15,430
With your permission...

664
01:06:16,973 --> 01:06:19,533
I could get the men together...

665
01:06:20,977 --> 01:06:26,176
and wipe those Breves
from the face of this earth,

666
01:06:26,215 --> 01:06:29,150
MR. FERREIRA: I'll repeat this
one last time,

667
01:06:29,185 --> 01:06:32,450
Blood has the same volume
for everyone.

668
01:06:32,488 --> 01:06:36,948
You have no right to take more
than the blood taken from you.

669
01:06:36,993 --> 01:06:42,522
Otherwise, you'll pay twice--
in this life and in the next.

670
01:06:45,701 --> 01:06:49,501
That's what my father taught me
and his father taught him.

671
01:06:52,041 --> 01:06:55,067
And that's how it'll be
until I die.

672
01:06:55,111 --> 01:06:57,079
[Liquid boiling]

673
01:07:14,497 --> 01:07:17,432
I taught you how to fly
with this, remember?

674
01:07:20,436 --> 01:07:22,063
You were scared shitless.

675
01:07:22,104 --> 01:07:23,765
[Both chuckle]

676
01:07:29,845 --> 01:07:32,973
Tonio, today it's your turn.

677
01:07:33,015 --> 01:07:34,141
Huh?

678
01:07:34,183 --> 01:07:36,845
You take my place,
I'll take yours.

679
01:07:36,886 --> 01:07:38,478
No, I don't want to.

680
01:07:38,521 --> 01:07:40,045
PACU: Just once.

681
01:07:40,089 --> 01:07:42,057
[Ropes creaking]

682
01:07:45,594 --> 01:07:47,357
[Laughs]

683
01:08:24,934 --> 01:08:27,368
[Pacu laughing]

684
01:08:37,746 --> 01:08:40,078
[Rope creaking]

685
01:08:40,116 --> 01:08:42,084
[Tearing]

686
01:08:43,786 --> 01:08:45,219
[Snap]

687
01:08:45,254 --> 01:08:46,721
[Thud]
TONIO: Ooh!

688
01:08:46,755 --> 01:08:49,087
[Whimpers]

689
01:08:49,125 --> 01:08:50,752
PACU: Tonio!

690
01:08:50,793 --> 01:08:52,852
[Running footsteps]

691
01:08:56,298 --> 01:08:59,358
Tonio. Tonio.

692
01:09:02,771 --> 01:09:05,569
Tonio. Tonio.

693
01:09:05,608 --> 01:09:06,802
Huh!

694
01:09:06,842 --> 01:09:08,969
[Both laughing]

695
01:09:12,815 --> 01:09:14,305
You're too damn strong.

696
01:09:14,350 --> 01:09:17,285
No, you just forgot how to fly.

697
01:09:17,319 --> 01:09:19,253
[Both laughing]

698
01:09:22,158 --> 01:09:24,149
[Mother laughing]

699
01:09:35,704 --> 01:09:38,502
[Father laughing]

700
01:09:49,552 --> 01:09:51,349
[Crowd cheering and clapping]

701
01:09:53,222 --> 01:09:57,022
Let me, it's my turn!
Ooh, it's hot!

702
01:10:01,063 --> 01:10:02,428
[Crowd cheers louder]

703
01:10:02,464 --> 01:10:04,125
Ha ha!

704
01:10:04,166 --> 01:10:06,657
[Crowd reacts]

705
01:10:11,440 --> 01:10:13,101
SALUSTIANA: Hey!

706
01:10:13,142 --> 01:10:14,700
[Crowd clapping]

707
01:10:15,978 --> 01:10:19,038
This is my favorite part
of the show.

708
01:10:19,081 --> 01:10:21,208
[Money rattling]

709
01:10:21,250 --> 01:10:23,013
Ha ha!

710
01:10:23,052 --> 01:10:25,520
Come on! Who's next!

711
01:10:25,554 --> 01:10:28,819
Keep filling it!
Fill it up!

712
01:10:28,857 --> 01:10:31,724
[Wind blowing]

713
01:10:31,760 --> 01:10:33,489
[Fire crackling]

714
01:10:33,529 --> 01:10:35,520
[People talking]

715
01:10:49,678 --> 01:10:51,509
You can't do this.

716
01:10:55,851 --> 01:10:57,978
Anyhow, he's already dead.

717
01:10:59,788 --> 01:11:01,915
But I'm not.

718
01:11:09,565 --> 01:11:11,260
[Jingling]

719
01:11:11,300 --> 01:11:13,097
[Footsteps]

720
01:11:23,779 --> 01:11:25,804
It's turned yellow.

721
01:11:30,419 --> 01:11:33,411
MR. FERREIRA:
Is it really yellow now?

722
01:11:33,455 --> 01:11:35,514
MAN: Yes, it's yellowed,

723
01:11:37,459 --> 01:11:38,949
[Bird chirps]

724
01:11:45,968 --> 01:11:48,368
You know what you
have to do, then.

725
01:11:53,642 --> 01:11:55,735
Yes, I know.

726
01:12:03,986 --> 01:12:08,946
Tonio, you know
the truce ends today.

727
01:12:10,659 --> 01:12:13,594
From now on,
it depends on the shirt.

728
01:12:15,364 --> 01:12:17,127
Don't go too far from the house.

729
01:12:18,667 --> 01:12:23,570
Stay close to me,
And always carry the gun,

730
01:12:23,605 --> 01:12:26,301
[Thunder]

731
01:12:29,445 --> 01:12:30,605
[Bird chirps]

732
01:12:30,646 --> 01:12:32,841
It's going to rain.

733
01:12:32,881 --> 01:12:35,281
No, it's not the rainy season.

734
01:12:35,317 --> 01:12:37,478
I know it's going to rain.

735
01:12:43,459 --> 01:12:44,790
Tonio?

736
01:12:46,995 --> 01:12:48,690
Pa took my book.

737
01:12:48,731 --> 01:12:50,699
[Thunder]

738
01:12:50,733 --> 01:12:54,499
I can't remember the story
or the mermaid's face anymore.

739
01:12:54,536 --> 01:12:56,561
[Sighs]

740
01:12:59,208 --> 01:13:01,233
[Wind blowing]

741
01:13:05,381 --> 01:13:08,043
The mermaid...

742
01:13:08,083 --> 01:13:10,483
[Hinges squeak and slam]

743
01:13:10,519 --> 01:13:14,319
Had a fish tail...

744
01:13:14,356 --> 01:13:20,920
while the boy had
toes, feet, and...

745
01:13:23,599 --> 01:13:25,396
[Tonio sighs]

746
01:13:26,468 --> 01:13:28,993
Aren't you going to sleep, Pacu?

747
01:13:29,037 --> 01:13:31,699
I can't, Tonio. It's too windy.

748
01:13:31,740 --> 01:13:34,004
[Sighs]

749
01:13:35,744 --> 01:13:37,177
Then talk in silence.

750
01:13:37,212 --> 01:13:39,407
OK.

751
01:13:39,448 --> 01:13:41,439
[Wind whistling]

752
01:13:49,391 --> 01:13:51,382
[Creaking]

753
01:14:15,851 --> 01:14:17,512
Tonio.

754
01:14:40,776 --> 01:14:42,767
[Wind blowing]

755
01:15:05,667 --> 01:15:07,328
Clara...

756
01:15:11,473 --> 01:15:14,340
I wanted to tell you
I've left everything.

757
01:15:18,480 --> 01:15:20,471
I'm heading east, to the coast.

758
01:15:27,022 --> 01:15:29,456
You have the right
to do it, too.

759
01:15:35,197 --> 01:15:37,859
[Thunder]

760
01:15:52,214 --> 01:15:54,045
[Thunder]

761
01:16:01,590 --> 01:16:05,117
[Thunder]

762
01:16:16,138 --> 01:16:17,662
[Rips]

763
01:16:17,706 --> 01:16:19,674
[Thunder]

764
01:17:23,171 --> 01:17:25,196
[Water dripping]

765
01:17:40,355 --> 01:17:42,016
[Whinnies]

766
01:18:05,514 --> 01:18:07,448
[Thunder]

767
01:18:17,459 --> 01:18:19,450
[Rain falling]

768
01:18:42,684 --> 01:18:44,675
[Water dripping]

769
01:18:49,157 --> 01:18:51,057
I'll be waiting.

770
01:19:22,057 --> 01:19:25,652
[Footsteps]

771
01:20:07,969 --> 01:20:09,095
[Thunder]

772
01:20:09,137 --> 01:20:11,298
[Horse whinnies]

773
01:20:42,003 --> 01:20:44,233
[Ragged breathing]

774
01:21:03,758 --> 01:21:05,749
[Crickets chirping]

775
01:21:29,684 --> 01:21:30,673
[Footsteps]

776
01:21:30,719 --> 01:21:32,710
[Ragged breathing]

777
01:21:37,893 --> 01:21:39,986
[Thunder]

778
01:21:42,264 --> 01:21:44,255
[Footsteps]

779
01:21:48,069 --> 01:21:53,029
PACU: Now you know my story,

780
01:21:53,074 --> 01:21:56,703
But I still can't
remember the other one,

781
01:21:56,745 --> 01:22:02,342
The mermaid, the shipsdamn!

782
01:22:04,352 --> 01:22:09,016
The kid couldn't find
the mermaid...

783
01:22:09,057 --> 01:22:11,287
no, it wasn't like that,

784
01:22:12,460 --> 01:22:13,927
Damn,

785
01:22:15,597 --> 01:22:21,331
It's the mermaid who came
looking--yeah, that's it,

786
01:22:21,369 --> 01:22:23,860
I think I'm remembering it!

787
01:22:23,905 --> 01:22:25,338
[Pacu sobbing]

788
01:22:27,309 --> 01:22:33,771
One day, the mermaid came
and took him to live with her,

789
01:22:33,815 --> 01:22:36,375
And he really liked that!

790
01:22:36,418 --> 01:22:38,818
She turned the kid
into a fish...

791
01:22:38,853 --> 01:22:42,721
and took him to live
in the east, at the sea,

792
01:22:42,757 --> 01:22:47,353
In the sea, everyone wasn't
dying all the time,

793
01:22:47,395 --> 01:22:49,522
There was a lot of room
for everyone,

794
01:22:50,765 --> 01:22:55,600
In the sea, they lived
so happily...

795
01:22:55,637 --> 01:22:59,903
so happily, they couldn't
stop laughing,

796
01:22:59,941 --> 01:23:01,033
Ha ha ha!

797
01:23:01,076 --> 01:23:03,271
Ha ha ha,

798
01:23:03,311 --> 01:23:05,040
[Sobbing]

799
01:23:05,080 --> 01:23:06,513
[Rustling footsteps]

800
01:23:08,016 --> 01:23:09,347
[Thunder]

801
01:23:09,384 --> 01:23:11,545
[Horse whinnies]

802
01:23:11,586 --> 01:23:14,384
[Pacu laughing]

803
01:23:20,695 --> 01:23:25,462
In the sea, they were so happy,
so happy together...

804
01:23:25,500 --> 01:23:28,469
they couldn't help laughing.

805
01:23:28,503 --> 01:23:31,904
[Pacu laughing]

806
01:23:34,242 --> 01:23:36,301
[Breathing heavily]

807
01:23:42,117 --> 01:23:44,915
[Gunshot]

808
01:23:53,628 --> 01:23:55,755
[Gasping]

809
01:24:05,073 --> 01:24:07,007
[Sobbing]

810
01:24:21,589 --> 01:24:23,147
[Hinges squeak, door slams]

811
01:24:26,928 --> 01:24:27,895
MOTHER: Tonio!

812
01:24:27,929 --> 01:24:31,865
Oh, God, not my son!

813
01:24:31,900 --> 01:24:34,391
Not my son!

814
01:24:34,436 --> 01:24:36,996
[Yelling in Portuguese]

815
01:24:37,038 --> 01:24:39,029
[Crickets chirping]

816
01:24:42,043 --> 01:24:43,203
[Sniffs]

817
01:24:51,653 --> 01:24:53,678
[Sniffs]

818
01:24:53,721 --> 01:24:55,712
[Birds chirping]

819
01:25:05,533 --> 01:25:07,467
[Sobbing]

820
01:25:17,545 --> 01:25:19,536
[Mother gasping]

821
01:25:21,883 --> 01:25:23,874
[Father sobbing]

822
01:25:27,789 --> 01:25:31,054
FATHER: They've killed the kid.

823
01:25:31,092 --> 01:25:32,957
[Footsteps]

824
01:25:36,631 --> 01:25:39,099
Get the gun, Tonio! Right now!

825
01:25:39,134 --> 01:25:41,728
There's no truce,
go avenge the blood!

826
01:25:41,769 --> 01:25:43,760
Reclaim the blood of those pigs!

827
01:25:46,508 --> 01:25:49,136
Go, my son! Reclaim the blood!

828
01:25:49,177 --> 01:25:50,735
Immediately!

829
01:25:50,778 --> 01:25:52,769
[Footsteps]

830
01:25:58,853 --> 01:26:01,583
FATHER: What are you doing?
The gun!

831
01:26:01,623 --> 01:26:04,217
Where's the gun, Tonio?

832
01:26:04,259 --> 01:26:05,317
Tonio!

833
01:26:05,360 --> 01:26:07,453
[Running footsteps]
Tonio!

834
01:26:08,563 --> 01:26:11,157
Come back!

835
01:26:11,199 --> 01:26:13,064
[Raspy breathing]

836
01:26:14,502 --> 01:26:17,801
Come back or you'll die
for the honor of the family.

837
01:26:17,839 --> 01:26:18,806
[Gunshot]

838
01:26:18,840 --> 01:26:23,174
It's over! Don't you see?

839
01:26:23,211 --> 01:26:25,543
It's all over!

840
01:26:25,580 --> 01:26:27,912
[Speaking Portuguese
and sobbing]

841
01:26:29,951 --> 01:26:32,613
[Gasping]

842
01:26:32,654 --> 01:26:34,622
[Both crying]

843
01:26:35,790 --> 01:26:37,223
FATHER: Oh, God.

844
01:26:39,294 --> 01:26:40,921
Oh, my God.

845
01:26:42,664 --> 01:26:44,529
[Grass crunching underfoot]

846
01:26:44,566 --> 01:26:46,591
[Wind blowing]

847
01:27:16,197 --> 01:27:19,189
[Waves crashing]

848
01:27:44,225 --> 01:27:48,161
PACU: One day...

849
01:27:48,196 --> 01:27:51,427
the mermaid took him to live
with her by the sea,

850
01:28:36,944 --> 01:28:39,936
[Waves crashing]

